    <p>To pro­tect young chil­dren from Covid-19, we con­tinue to en­cour­age young chil­dren to wear a mask or face shield, es­pe­cially if they’re in a group set­ting, for ex­am­ple, in pre-school... Chil­dren and other per­sons who may not have the co­or­di­na­tion nec­es­sary for the proper use of masks... should con­tinue to be su­per­vised.</p>
    <p>AS­SO­CI­ATE PRO­FES­SOR KEN­NETH MAK, MOH’s di­rec­tor of med­i­cal ser­vices.</p>


